# Implementation Plan - Fix Startup Hang (Port Detection)

The Paperclip dev server is hanging because the embedded PostgreSQL port detection logic is failing to accurately identify if the port is in use. Specifically, it checks `localhost` (which might only check IPv6 `::1`), while the database might be bound to IPv4 `127.0.0.1`. This leads to attempts to start multiple instances in the same data directory, causing a hang.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Robust Port Detection
I will update the port detection logic to be more conservative and check both IPv4 and IPv6, or use a wildcard bind for the check.

#### [MODIFY] [migration-runtime.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/packages/db/src/migration-runtime.ts)
- Update `isPortInUse` to listen on `0.0.0.0` for the check, ensuring it detects anything on IPv4. (IPv6 will be implicitly handled if the OS supports dual-stack).
- Also update `findAvailablePort` to be more robust.

### 2. Cleanup & Restart
I will perform a deep cleanup of all processes and restart the setup.

